Motivation
Prepare the project for production by adding a lockfile and updating deployment configuration and docs to match the repository layout.
Tighten API surface and observability by adding an origin allowlist for browser clients, request IDs and security headers.
Prevent internal error information leakage and centralize error logging across routes.
Remove Cloud Functions deployment references because the repo runs as a standalone src/ server.
Description
Added package-lock.json to lock dependencies for reproducible installs and supply-chain scanning.
Updated firebase.json to remove the functions block and removed the deploy:functions npm script from package.json to reflect that the project runs from src/.
Updated docs/deployment-guide.md and .env.example to document CORS_ORIGINS and to use src/index.js in the PM2 ecosystem example.
Implemented production-safe CORS handling in src/index.js via buildCorsOptions() that reads CORS_ORIGINS, switched to app.use(cors(...)), added generation/propagation of X-Request-Id (uses nanoid), and set additional security headers (X-Content-Type-Options, X-Frame-Options, Referrer-Policy).
Added centralized error handling improvements: enhanced global error handler to include requestId and hide raw error messages in production, and added internalError() helper in src/routes/* to standardize logging and responses.
Added docs/production-audit-2026-03-29.md documenting a preliminary audit and blockers.